Title: We're Going to Need More Wine
Author: Gabrielle Union
My Review:
While randomly scrolling YouTube for what to entertain myself with while having breakfast, Gabrielle Union's interview with Trevor Noah on The Daily Show caught my eye and so I gave it a try. I enjoyed the interview and decided to read the book myself.

Gabrielle Union has proven that she's not only a talented actress with a beautiful face that doesn't age but a strong, powerful, intelligent black woman as well.

Her book takes you through experiences and mistakes as a young black girl trying to get through school to the amazing woman she is today with her own share of challenges she's experienced along the way. This book is one of those unputdownable types that leaves you wanting more and more.
Her sense of humour is amazing and the book gives this down to earth, big sister vibe with just the right amount of cussing.

I really enjoyed it.
